question:
District category contains Academic District, Medical District, and Arts District.
Supermarkets category contains Dollar General, H-E-B, and Auchan.
Product category contains Buttermilk, Canned Artichokes, and Brownies.
The number of each Arts District 's H-E-B equals each Auchan 's Canned Artichokes.
The number of each Dollar General 's Canned Artichokes equals the sum of each Auchan 's Canned Artichokes, each H-E-B 's Brownies, and each Academic District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each H-E-B 's Canned Artichokes equals the sum of each Dollar General 's Canned Artichokes, each Academic District 's Auchan, each Dollar General 's Brownies, and each Academic District 's H-E-B.
The number of each Arts District 's Auchan equals the sum of each Academic District 's Dollar General, each Dollar General 's Buttermilk, and each Auchan 's Brownies.
The number of each H-E-B 's Brownies equals 9 times the sum of each Medical District 's H-E-B and each Auchan 's Canned Artichokes.
The number of each Academic District 's Auchan equals 12.
The number of each H-E-B 's Buttermilk equals 5.
The number of each Auchan 's Canned Artichokes equals the sum of each Academic District 's Auchan, each Academic District 's Supermarkets, and each Academic District 's H-E-B.
The number of each Medical District 's H-E-B equals the sum of each Dollar General 's Buttermilk, each Academic District 's Dollar General, and each Academic District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Academic District 's H-E-B equals 5 more than the difference of each Academic District 's Auchan and each Academic District 's Dollar General.
The number of each Dollar General 's Brownies equals 19.
The number of each Dollar General 's Buttermilk equals each Auchan 's Canned Artichokes.
The number of each Medical District 's Auchan equals the sum of each Dollar General 's Buttermilk, each Dollar General 's Product, each Auchan 's Canned Artichokes, and each Arts District 's H-E-B.
The number of each Auchan 's Brownies equals each Dollar General 's Brownies.
The number of each Academic District 's Dollar General equals each Academic District 's Auchan.
The number of each Auchan 's Buttermilk equals each Dollar General 's Canned Artichokes.
How many Brownies does H-E-B have?
solution:
Define each Academic District 's Auchan as p; So p = 12.
Define each Academic District 's Dollar General as J; So J = p = 12.
Define each Academic District 's H-E-B as S; W = p - J = 12 - 12 = 0; So S = 5 + W = 5 + 0 = 5.
Define each Academic District 's Supermarkets as i; z = p + J = 12 + 12 = 1; So i = S + z = 5 + 1 = 6.
Define each Auchan 's Canned Artichokes as v; t = S + p = 5 + 12 = 17; So v = i + t = 6 + 17 = 0.
Define each Dollar General 's Buttermilk as K; So K = v = 0.
Define each Medical District 's H-E-B as q; X = J + i = 12 + 6 = 18; So q = K + X = 0 + 18 = 18.
Define each H-E-B 's Brownies as x; c = q + v = 18 + 0 = 18; So x = 9 * c = 9 * 18 = 1.
